Package aoop.asteroids.udp.packets

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GameStatePacket
    The GameStatePacket is sent by the Server whenever the game-state has changed.
    MessageListPacket
    The MessageListPacket only contains a list of messages that all Clients should see.
    Packet
    The default Packet class, where all packet types inherit from.
    These packets are supposed to be sent over UDP.
    Internally, they are made up of a String, which is built from JSON.

    All inherited classes should define a Constructor, which takes zero or more objects and constructs a packet containing that objects's important data
    And a public static decodePacket() method, that should take a JSONArray as input, and return the important information from this packet.
    PlayerJoinPacket
    This packet is sent by the Client whenever a Player wants to join a game.
    PlayerUpdatePacket
    Sent by a Player multiple time per second.
    SpectateJoinPacket
    This packet is sent by the Client whenever a Spectator wants to join a game.
    SpectatorPingPacket
    Sent by the Spectator every few milliseconds, to let the Server know that the Spectator is still listening to the connection, and watching the game.
    Does not contain actual data, as only the timestamp of the Packet is needed in this case.
